<title> The Cortical Activity of Graded Relevance

<desc> Description:
IR systems have employed various techniques to capture the subjective aspect of relevance [2] to improve the effectiveness of retrieved results. Examples of such techniques are explicit [38], implicit (e.g.[24, 36]) and physiological [47] feedback.

