<title> The Cortical Activity of Graded Relevance

<desc> Description:
Despite significant attention dedicated to examining this concept, relevance is still not fully understood, and it is a subject of many ongoing scientific debates. Past research has investigated the concept of relevance at different granularity levels from both the user [29, 71] and system [35, 40] perspective. Within the system side, graded relevance (in comparison to the binary one) has been shown to improve ranking functions [34, 55].

